/*
Depression Remission or Response for Adolescents and Adults (DRR)
*/library DRR_FHIR version '1.0.0'

//using FHIR version '3.0.1'

using FHIR version '3.0.0'

/*
Measure Description
The percentage of members 12 years of age and older with a diagnosis of
		depression and an elevated PHQ-9 score, who had evidence of
		response or remission within 5 to 7 months of the elevated score.
		Three rates are reported.
	1. Follow-Up PHQ-9. The percentage of members who have a follow-up
		PHQ-9 score documented within the five to seven months after the
		initial elevated PHQ-9 score.
	2. Depression Remission. The percentage of members who achieved remission
		within five to seven months after the initial elevated PHQ-9 score.
	3. Depression Response. The percentage of members who showed response
		within five to seven months after the initial elevated PHQ-9 score.
*/

codesystem "LOINC": 'http://loinc.org'
codesystem "SNOMED": 'http://snomed.info/sct'
codesystem "CQFramework": 'http://cqframework.info/codesystem/placeholder'

// valueset "Personality Disorder": 'urn:oid:2.16.840.1.113883.3.67.1.101.1.246' // Grouping Value Set
// valueset "Pervasive Developmental Disorder": 'urn:oid:2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1003.105.12.1152' // User Defined QDM Value Set
// valueset "Bipolar Disorder": 'urn:oid:2.16.840.1.113883.3.67.1.101.1.128' // Grouping Value Set
// valueset "Psychotic Disorder": 'urn:oid:2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1003.105.12.1153' // User Defined QDM Value Set
// valueset "Interactive Outpatient Encounter": 'urn:oid:2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1003.101.12.1074'
// valueset "PHQ-9 Tool": 'urn:oid:2.16.840.1.113883.3.67.1.101.11.723' // Grouping Value Set
// valueset "PHQ-9 Modified Score": 'urn:oid:2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1003.105.12.1154' // Grouping Value Set

// update

valueset "Bipolar Disorder": '2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1044'
valueset "Bipolar Disorder ECDS": '2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1346'
// valueset "Hospice": '2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1418'
valueset "Interactive Outpatient Encounter": '2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1347'
valueset "Major Depression and Dysthymia": '2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1351'
valueset "Other Bipolar Disorder": '2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1399'
valueset "Personality Disorder": '2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1355'
valueset "Pervasive Developmental Disorder": '2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1356'
valueset "PHQ-9 Total Score": '2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1401'
valueset "Psychotic Disorder": '2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1352'

// code "Major Depression and Dysthymia": '78667006' from "SNOMED"

code "PHQ-9 Modified Score": '00009' from "CQFramework"
code "PHQ-9 Tool": '44249-1' from "LOINC"

/*
This library has an explicit parameter which is the measurement year.
While the actual parameter's type accepts all intervals, this library
expects it will only be given arguments corresponding exactly to one whole
calendar year, and it will not behave properly otherwise; 2017 for example:
Interval[DateTime(2017,1,1,0,0,0,0), DateTime(2018,1,1,0,0,0,0))
*/

parameter "Measurement Period" Interval<DateTime>

// Intake Period: June 1 of the year prior to the measurement period through May 31 of the measurement period.

define "Intake Period As MP Shifted Back 7 Months":
  Interval[start of "Measurement Period" - 7 months, 
  end of "Measurement Period" - 7 months )

define "Intake Period Union Measurement Period":
  Interval[start of "Measurement Period" - 7 months, 
  end of "Measurement Period" - 7 months )

/*
This library evaluates with respect to exactly 1 candidate patient at a time,
that patient being given by the special context parameter Patient.
*/

context Patient

/*
Initial Population
Product lines -- Commercial, Medicaid, Medicare (report each product line separately).
*/

define "Initial Population":
  AgeInYearsAt(start of "Measurement Period")>= 12
    and exists ( "DRR Encounter" DRR
        with [DiagnosticReport: "Major Depression and Dysthymia"] DepressionDiagnosis
          such that DepressionDiagnosis.status.value in { 'preliminary', 'final', 'amended', 'corrected', 'appended' }
            and PeriodToIntervalOfDT(DepressionDiagnosis.effective)overlaps day of PeriodToIntervalOfDT(DRR.period)
    )

define "DRR Encounter":
  [Encounter: "Interactive Outpatient Encounter"] DRR
    where DRR.status.value in { 'planned', 'arrived', 'triaged', 'in-progress', 'onleave', 'finished' }
      and PeriodToIntervalOfDT(DRR.period)during day of "Intake Period As MP Shifted Back 7 Months"

/*
Exclusions
*/

define "Denominator Exclusion":
  exists ( distinct ( [DiagnosticReport: "Bipolar Disorder"]
					// TODO: The spec mentions 3 Bipolar valuesets, which are like
					// the ones in DSF, but it only gives OIDs for one of the 3
					// and that OID is different than any in DSF.
					// Note that DMS and DRR are in the same boat.
      union [DiagnosticReport: "Personality Disorder"]
      union [DiagnosticReport: "Psychotic Disorder"]
      union [DiagnosticReport: "Pervasive Developmental Disorder"] ) D
      where D.status.value in { 'preliminary', 'final', 'amended', 'corrected', 'appended' }
        and PeriodToIntervalOfDT(D.effective)overlaps day of "Intake Period Union Measurement Period"
  )

/*
Denominators and Numerators
*/

// Depression Follow-Up

define "Denominator 1":
  "Initial Population"
    and exists ( "DRR Encounter" )
    and "Depression Index" is not null

// Depression Follow-Up

define "Numerator 1":
  "Initial Population"
    and exists ( "PHQ-9 Assessments" PHQ
        with "Depression Index" DI
          such that PHQ.effective.value after day of DI.effective.value
            and days between DI.effective.value and PHQ.effective.value >= 150
            and days between DI.effective.value and PHQ.effective.value <= 210
        return PHQ
    )

// Depression Remission

define "Denominator 2":
  "Denominator 1"

// Depression Remission

define "Numerator 2":
  "Initial Population"
    and exists ( "PHQ-9 Assessments" PHQ
        with "Depression Index" DI
          such that ( PHQ.value as Quantity ).value.value < 5
            and PHQ.effective.value after day of DI.effective.value
            and days between DI.effective.value and PHQ.effective.value >= 150
            and days between DI.effective.value and PHQ.effective.value <= 210
        return PHQ
    )

// Depression Response

define "Denominator 3":
  "Denominator 1"

// Depression Response

define "Numerator 3":
  "Initial Population"
    and exists ( "PHQ-9 Assessments" PHQ
        with "Depression Index" DI
          such that ( PHQ.value as Quantity ).value.value <= ( DI.value as Quantity ).value.value / 2
            and PHQ.effective.value after day of DI.effective.value
            and days between DI.effective.value and PHQ.effective.value >= 150
            and days between DI.effective.value and PHQ.effective.value <= 210
        return PHQ
    )

define "Depression Index":
  First("PHQ-9 Assessments" PHQ
      with "DRR Encounter" DRR
        such that(PHQ.value as Quantity).value.value > 9
          and((PHQ.effective.value same day or before start of PeriodToIntervalOfDT(DRR.period)
                and days between PHQ.effective.value and start of PeriodToIntervalOfDT(DRR.period)<= 15
            )
              or(PHQ.effective.value same day or after start of PeriodToIntervalOfDT(DRR.period)
                  and days between start of PeriodToIntervalOfDT(DRR.period)and PHQ.effective.value <= 15
              )
          )
      return PHQ
  )

define "PHQ-9 Assessments":
  distinct ( [Observation: "PHQ-9 Tool"]
    union [Observation: "PHQ-9 Modified Score"] ) PHQ
    where PHQ.status.value in { 'final', 'amended' }
      and PHQ.value is not null

/*
Stratifiers
*/

define "Stratifier 1":
  AgeInYearsAt(start of "Measurement Period")in Interval[12, 17]

define "Stratifier 2":
  AgeInYearsAt(start of "Measurement Period")in Interval[18, 44]

define "Stratifier 3":
  AgeInYearsAt(start of "Measurement Period")in Interval[45, 64]

define "Stratifier 4":
  AgeInYearsAt(start of "Measurement Period")>= 65

/*
Utility Functions
*/

define function PeriodToIntervalOfDT(value FHIR.Period):
  Interval[value."start".value, value."end".value]

/*
Depression Screening and Follow-Up for Adolescents and Adults (DSF)
*/library DSF_FHIR version '1.0.0'

//using FHIR version '3.0.1'

using FHIR version '3.0.0'

/*
Measure Description
The percentage of members 12 years of age and older who were screened for
		clinical depression using a standardized tool and, if screened positive,
		who received appropriate follow-up care. Two rates are reported.
	1. Depression Screening. The percentage of members who were screened for
		clinical depression using a standardized tool.
	2. Follow-Up on Positive Screen. The percentage of members who screened
		positive for depression and received appropriate follow-up care within 30 days.
*/

codesystem "LOINC": 'http://loinc.org'
codesystem "SNOMED": 'http://snomed.info/sct'
codesystem "CQFramework": 'http://cqframework.info/codesystem/placeholder'

// valueset "Bipolar Disorder": 'urn:oid:2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1044' // Grouping Value Set
// valueset "Bipolar Disorder ECDS": 'urn:oid:2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1346' // Grouping Value Set
// valueset "Other Bipolar Disorder": 'urn:oid:2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1399' // Grouping Value Set
// valueset "Behavioral Health Encounter": 'urn:oid:2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1383' // Grouping Value Set
// valueset "Depression Case Management Encounter": 'urn:oid:2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1389' // Grouping Value Set
// valueset "ECDS Follow-Up Visit": 'urn:oid:2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1385' // Grouping Value Set
// valueset "Depression Screen": 'urn:oid:2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1384' // Grouping Value Set
// valueset "Positive Depression Screen": 'urn:oid:2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1387' // Grouping Value Set
// valueset "Negative Depression Screen": 'urn:oid:2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1386' // Grouping Value Set
// valueset "Antidepressant Medication": 'TODO' // not in spec Data Criteria

// update

valueset "Behavioral Health Encounter": '2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1383'
valueset "Bipolar Disorder": '2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1044'
valueset "Bipolar Disorder ECDS": '2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1346'
valueset "Depression": '2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1390'
valueset "Depression Case Management Encounter": '2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1389'
valueset "Depression Screen": '2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1384'
valueset "ECDS Follow-Up Visit": '2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1385'
// valueset "Hospice": '2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1418'
valueset "Mental Illness": '2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1179'
valueset "Mental Illness SNOMED": '2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1453'
valueset "Negative Depression Screen": '2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1386'
valueset "Other Bipolar Disorder": '2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1399'
valueset "Positive Depression Screen": '2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1387'
valueset "Major Depression and Dysthymia": '2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1351'

code "Antidepressant Medication": '00001' from "CQFramework"
code "PHQ-9 Modified Score": '00009' from "CQFramework"
code "PHQ-9 Tool": '44249-1' from "LOINC"

/*
This library has an explicit parameter which is the measurement year.
While the actual parameter's type accepts all intervals, this library
expects it will only be given arguments corresponding exactly to one whole
calendar year, and it will not behave properly otherwise; 2017 for example:
Interval[DateTime(2017,1,1,0,0,0,0), DateTime(2018,1,1,0,0,0,0))
*/

parameter "Measurement Period" Interval<DateTime>

define "First Predecessor Year":
  Interval[start of "Measurement Period" - 1 year, start of "Measurement Period" )

define "Lookback Interval One More Year":
  Interval[start of "Measurement Period" - 1 year, 
  end of "Measurement Period" )

/*
This library evaluates with respect to exactly 1 candidate patient at a time,
that patient being given by the special context parameter Patient.
*/

context Patient

/*
Initial Population
Product lines -- Commercial, Medicaid, Medicare (report each product line separately).
*/

define "Initial Population":
  AgeInYearsAt(start of "Measurement Period")>= 12

/*
Exclusions
*/

define "Denominator Exclusion":
  exists ( "Bipolar Disorder Reports" BD
      where BD.status.value in { 'preliminary', 'final', 'amended', 'corrected', 'appended' }
        and PeriodToIntervalOfDT(BD.effective)overlaps day of "Lookback Interval One More Year"
  )
    or exists ( [DiagnosticReport: "Major Depression and Dysthymia"] MDD
        where MDD.status.value in { 'preliminary', 'final', 'amended', 'corrected', 'appended' }
          and PeriodToIntervalOfDT(MDD.effective)overlaps day of "First Predecessor Year"
    )

define "Bipolar Disorder Reports":
  [DiagnosticReport: "Bipolar Disorder"]
    union [DiagnosticReport: "Bipolar Disorder ECDS"]
    union [DiagnosticReport: "Other Bipolar Disorder"]

/*
Denominators and Numerators
*/

// Depression Screening

define "Denominator 1":
  "Initial Population"

// Depression Screening

define "Numerator 1":
  "Initial Population"
    and exists ( [Observation: "Depression Screen"] DepressionScreen
        where DepressionScreen.status.value in { 'final', 'amended' }
          and DepressionScreen.effective.value in day of "Measurement Period"
    )

// Positive Follow-Up

define "Denominator 2":
  "Initial Population"
    and exists ( "Positive Depression Screen During Follow-Up Period" )

// Positive Follow-Up

define "Numerator 2":
  "Initial Population"
    and ( exists ( "Dispensed Antidepressant Within 31 Days" )
        or exists ( "Follow-Up Encounter Within 31 Days" )
        or exists ( "Same Day Behavioral Encounter" )
        or exists ( "Negative Depression Screen Within 31 Days" )
    )

define "Positive Depression Screen During Follow-Up Period":
  [Observation: "Positive Depression Screen"] PositiveScreen
    where PositiveScreen.status.value in { 'final', 'amended' }
      and PositiveScreen.effective.value in day of "Measurement Period"

define "First Positive Depression Screen During Follow-Up Period":
  { First("Positive Depression Screen During Follow-Up Period" Obs
      sort by effective.value
  )}

define "Follow-Up Care Encounters":
  distinct ( [Encounter: "Behavioral Health Encounter"]
    union ( [Encounter: "ECDS Follow-Up Visit"] E
        with [DiagnosticReport: "Major Depression and Dysthymia"] D
          such that E.status.value in { 'planned', 'arrived', 'triaged', 'in-progress', 'onleave', 'finished' }
            and D.status.value in { 'preliminary', 'final', 'amended', 'corrected', 'appended' }
            and PeriodToIntervalOfDT(D.effective)overlaps day of PeriodToIntervalOfDT(E.period)
    )
    union [Encounter: "Depression Case Management Encounter"] ) Enc
    where Enc.status.value in { 'planned', 'arrived', 'triaged', 'in-progress', 'onleave', 'finished' }

define "Same Day Behavioral Encounter":
  [Encounter: "Behavioral Health Encounter"] BehavioralEncounter
    with "First Positive Depression Screen During Follow-Up Period" PositiveScreen
      such that BehavioralEncounter.status.value in { 'planned', 'arrived', 'triaged', 'in-progress', 'onleave', 'finished' }
        and start of PeriodToIntervalOfDT(BehavioralEncounter.period)same day as PositiveScreen.effective.value
    return BehavioralEncounter

define "Dispensed Antidepressant Within 31 Days":
  [MedicationDispense: medication in "Antidepressant Medication"] Antidepressants
    with "First Positive Depression Screen During Follow-Up Period" PositiveScreen
      such that Antidepressants.status.value = 'completed'
        and days between Antidepressants.whenHandedOver.value and PositiveScreen.effective.value <= 31
    return Antidepressants

define "Follow-Up Encounter Within 31 Days":
  "Follow-Up Care Encounters" FollowUps
    with "First Positive Depression Screen During Follow-Up Period" PositiveScreen
      such that days between start of PeriodToIntervalOfDT(FollowUps.period)and PositiveScreen.effective.value >= 1
        and days between start of PeriodToIntervalOfDT(FollowUps.period)and PositiveScreen.effective.value <= 31
    return FollowUps

define "Negative Depression Screen Within 31 Days":
  [Observation: "Negative Depression Screen"] NegativeScreen
    with "First Positive Depression Screen During Follow-Up Period" PositiveScreen
      such that NegativeScreen.status.value in { 'final', 'amended' }
        and days between NegativeScreen.effective.value and PositiveScreen.effective.value <= 31
    return NegativeScreen

/*
Stratifiers
*/

define "Stratifier 1":
  AgeInYearsAt(start of "Measurement Period")in Interval[12, 17]

define "Stratifier 2":
  AgeInYearsAt(start of "Measurement Period")in Interval[18, 44]

define "Stratifier 3":
  AgeInYearsAt(start of "Measurement Period")in Interval[45, 64]

define "Stratifier 4":
  AgeInYearsAt(start of "Measurement Period")>= 65

/*
Utility Functions
*/

define function PeriodToIntervalOfDT(value FHIR.Period):
  Interval[value."start".value, value."end".value]

library Participation version '1.0.0'

using FHIR version '3.0.0'

include FHIRHelpers version '3.0.0' called FHIRHelpers

valueset "NCQA Payer": 'http://ncqa.org/fhir/us/hedis/ValueSet/ncqa-payer' //'urn:oid:2.16.840.1.113762.1.4.1165.42'
valueset "Commercial": 'urn:oid:2.16.840.1.113762.1.4.1165.46'
valueset "Medicaid": 'urn:oid:2.16.840.1.113762.1.4.1165.45'
valueset "Medicare": 'urn:oid:2.16.840.1.113762.1.4.1165.44'

context Patient

define "Medicaid Product":
  'medicaid'

define "Commercial Product":
  'commercial'

define "Medicare Product":
  'medicare'

/*
  Report in the product line based on which product they are enrolled in at a given date
	(generally the end of the measurement period) but continuous enrollment calculations
	should consider all participation periods, regardless of product
	
	Input parameters:
		Product Line: The product line being reported
		Index Date: Generally measurement period, but could be tied to an event
		Participation Period: Generally one year, two years, or twenty seven months, but could be based on an event
		Allowed Gap Days: Generally 45 days, but could be 0
		
	Example 1 - One year continuously enrolled
		"Is Enrolled"(ProductLine, end of "Measurement Period", "Measurement Period", 45)
		
	Example 2 - Two years continuously enrolled
	  "Is Enrolled"(ProductLine, end of "Measurement Period", Interval[start of "Measurement Period" - 1 year, end of "Measurement Period"], 45)
		
	Example 3 - Twenty seven months continuously enrolled
		"Is Enrolled"(ProductLine, end of "Measurement Period", Interval[start of "Measurement Period" - 2 years - 3 months, end of "Measurement Period"], 45)
		
	Example 4 - Continuously enrolled surrounding an index event such as a heart attack
		"Is Enrolled"(ProductLine, "Date of Heart Attack", Interval["Date of Heart Attack", "Date of Heart Attack" + 18 months], 45)
		
	Example 5 - Continuously enrolled with no gaps during the 9 months prior to a birth and for the following year, allowing for a gap
	  "Is Enrolled"(ProductLine, "Date Of Delivery", Interval["Date Of Delivery" - 9 months, "Date Of Delivery"], 0)
		  and "Is Enrolled"(ProductLine, "Date Of Delivery", Interval["Date Of Delivery", "Date Of Delivery" + 1 year], 45)
*/

define function "Is Enrolled"(ProductLine String, IndexDate DateTime, ParticipationPeriod Interval<DateTime>, AllowedGapDays Integer):
  case
		/* If this is not running for a specific product line, ignore enrollment considerations */
    when ProductLine is null then true 
    else
			/* Is the patient enrolled in the given product line on the given index date? */ "Is Enrolled On Date"(ProductLine, IndexDate)
			/* Is the patient continuously enrolled in every year of the participation period */
    and AllTrue(("Enrollment Periods"(ParticipationPeriod))EnrollmentPeriod
        return "Is Continuously Enrolled In Period"(EnrollmentPeriod, if duration in months of EnrollmentPeriod >= 6 then AllowedGapDays 
            else 0
        )
    )
  end
	
/*
Returns all Commercial, Medicaid, and Medicare participation for the patient
*/

define "Participation":
  ["Coverage": type in "Commercial"]
    union ["Coverage": type in "Medicaid"]
    union ["Coverage": type in "Medicare"]

define function "Is Enrolled On Date"(ProductLine String, IndexDate DateTime):
  exists ( ( case ProductLine
      when "Commercial Product" then ["Coverage": type in "Commercial"]
      when "Medicare Product" then ["Coverage": type in "Medicare"]

/*
Pneumococcal Vaccination Status of Older Adults (PVS)
*/library PVS_FHIR version '1.0.0'

//using FHIR version '3.0.1'

using FHIR version '3.0.0'

/*
Measure Description
The percentage of members 65 years of age and older who have ever received
the recommended series of pneumococcal vaccines: 13-valent pneumococcal
conjugate vaccine (PCV13) and 23-valent pneumococcal polysaccharide vaccine (PPSV23).
*/

// valueset "Anaphylactic Reaction Due to Vaccine": 'urn:oid:2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1003.199.12.1027' // Grouping Value Set
// valueset "Cerebrospinal Fluid Leaks": 'urn:oid:1.1.1.1' // User Defined QDM Value Set
// valueset "Functional or Aplastic Anemia": 'urn:oid:1.1.1.1' // User Defined QDM Value Set
// valueset "Disorders of the Immune System": 'urn:oid:1.1.1.1' // User Defined QDM Value Set
// valueset "Pneumococcal Conjugate Vaccine 13": 'urn:oid:1.1.1.1' // User Defined QDM Value Set
// valueset "Pneumococcal Conjugate Vaccine 23": 'urn:oid:1.1.1.1' // User Defined QDM Value Set
// valueset "Bone Marrow Transplant": 'urn:oid:2.16.840.1.113883.3.666.5.336' // Grouping Value Set
// valueset "Chemotherapy": 'urn:oid:2.16.840.1.113762.1.4.1047.451' // Grouping Value Set
// valueset "Cochlear Implants": 'urn:oid:1.1.1.1' // User Defined QDM Value Set

// update

valueset "Anaphylactic Reaction Due to Serum": '2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1023'
valueset "Anaphylactic Reaction Due to Vaccine": '2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1024'
valueset "Bone Marrow Transplant": '2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1325'
valueset "Bone Marrow Transplant SNOMED": '2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1442'
valueset "Cerebrospinal Fluid Leaks": '2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1448'
valueset "Chemotherapy": '2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1326'
valueset "Chemotherapy SNOMED/CPT": '2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1441'
valueset "Cochlear Implants": '2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1447'
valueset "Disorders of the Immune System": '2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1139'
valueset "Functional or Aplastic Anemia": '2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1449'
// valueset "Hospice": '2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1418'
valueset "Pneumococcal Conjugate Vaccine 13": '2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1439'
valueset "Pneumococcal Conjugate Vaccine 23": '2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1004.1440'

/*
This library has an explicit parameter which is the measurement year.
While the actual parameter's type accepts all intervals, this library
expects it will only be given arguments corresponding exactly to one whole
calendar year, and it will not behave properly otherwise; 2017 for example:
Interval[DateTime(2017,1,1,0,0,0,0), DateTime(2018,1,1,0,0,0,0))
*/

parameter "Measurement Period" Interval<DateTime>

/*
This library evaluates with respect to exactly 1 candidate patient at a time,
that patient being given by the special context parameter Patient.
*/

context Patient

/*
Initial Population
Product lines -- Commercial, Medicaid, Medicare (report each product line separately).
*/

define "Initial Population":
  AgeInYearsAt(start of "Measurement Period")>= 65

/*
Exclusions
*/

define "Denominator Exclusion":
  exists ( "Chemotherapy and Bone Marrow Transplant Procedures" ProcedureUnion
      where ProcedureUnion.status.value in { 'in-progress', 'completed' }
        and PeriodToIntervalOfDT(ProcedureUnion.performed)overlaps day of "Measurement Period"
  )
    or exists ( [DiagnosticReport: "Anaphylactic Reaction Due to Vaccine"] ReactionToVaccine
        where ReactionToVaccine.status.value in { 'preliminary', 'final', 'amended', 'corrected', 'appended' }
          and start of PeriodToIntervalOfDT(ReactionToVaccine.effective)before day of "Measurement Period"
    )

define "Chemotherapy and Bone Marrow Transplant Procedures":
  [Procedure: "Chemotherapy"]
    union [Procedure: "Bone Marrow Transplant"]

/*
Denominators and Numerators
*/

define "Denominator":
  "Initial Population"

// TODO: The Numerator logic in the spec appears to have contradictions
// with the intent of the spec, such as AND meaning union vs intersection;
// this logic should be given another review.

define "Numerator":
  "Initial Population"
    and ( "PVC13 After Age 60 And Then PVC23 After 12 More Months"
        or "PVC13 After Age 2 And Then PVC23 After 8 More Weeks"
    )

define "PVC13 After Age 60 And Then PVC23 After 12 More Months":
  exists ( "Pneumococcal Vaccine 13 After Age 60" V13
      with "Pneumococcal Vaccine 23 After Age 60" V23
        such that months between V13."date".value and V23."date".value >= 12
  )

define "Pneumococcal Vaccine 13 After Age 60":
  [Immunization: "Pneumococcal Conjugate Vaccine 13"] V13
    where V13.status.value in { 'in-progress', 'completed' }
      and AgeInYearsAt(V13."date".value)>= 60

define "Pneumococcal Vaccine 23 After Age 60":
  [Immunization: "Pneumococcal Conjugate Vaccine 23"] V23
    where V23.status.value in { 'in-progress', 'completed' }
      and AgeInYearsAt(V23."date".value)>= 60

define "PVC13 After Age 2 And Then PVC23 After 8 More Weeks":
  "Immunocompromised Diagnoses or Cochlear Implants"
    and exists ( "Pneumococcal Vaccine 13 After Age 2" V13
        with "Pneumococcal Vaccine 23 After Age 2" V23
          such that weeks between V13."date".value and V23."date".value >= 8
    )

define "Pneumococcal Vaccine 13 After Age 2":
  [Immunization: "Pneumococcal Conjugate Vaccine 13"] V13
    where V13.status.value in { 'in-progress', 'completed' }
      and AgeInYearsAt(V13."date".value)>= 2

define "Pneumococcal Vaccine 23 After Age 2":
  [Immunization: "Pneumococcal Conjugate Vaccine 23"] V23
    where V23.status.value in { 'in-progress', 'completed' }
      and AgeInYearsAt(V23."date".value)>= 2

define "Immunocompromised Diagnoses or Cochlear Implants":
  exists ( "Immunocompromised Diagnoses Overlapping Measurement Period" )
    or exists ( "Cochlear Implants on or Before End of Measurement Period" )

define "Immunocompromised Diagnoses Overlapping Measurement Period":
  distinct ( [DiagnosticReport: "Cerebrospinal Fluid Leaks"]
    union [DiagnosticReport: "Functional or Aplastic Anemia"]
    union [DiagnosticReport: "Disorders of the Immune System"] ) D
    where D.status.value in { 'preliminary', 'final', 'amended', 'corrected', 'appended' }
      and PeriodToIntervalOfDT(D.effective)overlaps day of "Measurement Period"

define "Cochlear Implants on or Before End of Measurement Period":
  [Procedure: "Cochlear Implants"] CochlearImplant
    where CochlearImplant.status.value in { 'in-progress', 'completed' }
      and start of PeriodToIntervalOfDT(CochlearImplant.performed)same day or before 
      end of "Measurement Period"

/*
Stratifiers
*/

define "Stratifier 1":
  AgeInYearsAt(start of "Measurement Period")in Interval[65, 74]

define "Stratifier 2":
  AgeInYearsAt(start of "Measurement Period")in Interval[75, 84]

define "Stratifier 3":
  AgeInYearsAt(start of "Measurement Period")>= 85

/*
Utility Functions
*/

define function PeriodToIntervalOfDT(value FHIR.Period):
  Interval[value."start".value, value."end".value]

library WCCABA version '1'

using FHIR version '3.0.0'

include FHIRHelpers version '3.0.0' called FHIRHelpers

/*

BMI Percent	 WCC, ABA	 BMI percentile measurements
"BMI Percentile"
ICD10CM
2 years

Body Mass Index (BMI) Value	 ABA	 value identifying body mass
"BMI Value"
ICD10CM
2 years

Height	ABA, WCC	Value of height plus units, ie 70 inches or 5 feet 10 inches
No value set, but must be retrieved for ABA compliance data to be used in a standard supplmenetal data source according to NCQA General Guideline 34 under the heading 'Required Data Elements'
2 years

Weight	ABA, WCC	Value of weight plus units, ie 85 kg or 200 lbs
No value set, but must be retrieved for ABA compliance data to be used in a standard supplmenetal data source according to NCQA General Guideline 34 under the heading 'Required Data Elements'
2 years

Uses the DAF Profiles for Body Height/Body Weight
*/

valueset "BMI Percentile": 'BMI Percentile'
valueset "BMI Value": 'BMI Value'
valueset "Body Height": 'Body Height' // LOINC 8302-2
valueset "Body Weight": 'Body Weight' // LOINC 3141-9

parameter MeasurementPeriod Interval<DateTime>

context Patient

define "Lookback Interval Two Years":
  Interval[start of MeasurementPeriod - 2 years, 
  end of MeasurementPeriod]

// TODO: Need to verify the demographic here

define "In Demographic":
  AgeInYearsAt(start of MeasurementPeriod)>= 18

/* BMI Percent	 BMI percentile measurements */

define "BMI Percent":
  [Observation: "BMI Percentile"] P
    where P.status in { 'final', 'amended' }
      and P.effective during day of "Lookback Interval Two Years"

/* Body Mass Index (BMI) Value	  value identifying body mass */

define "Body Mass Index (BMI) Value":
  [Observation: "BMI Value"] V
    where V.status in { 'final', 'amended' }
      and V.effective during day of "Lookback Interval Two Years"

/* Height */

define "Height":
  [Observation: "Body Height"] O
    where O.status in { 'final', 'amended' }
      and O.effective during day of "Lookback Interval Two Years"

/* Body Weight */

define "Weight":
  [Observation: "Body Weight"] O
    where O.status in { 'final', 'amended' }
      and O.effective during day of "Lookback Interval Two Years"
